{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 12:50:51.237085", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- localized faulty devices: server_access_router, load_balancer\n- selected root cause(s): ospf_area_misconfiguration, load_balancer_overload\n\nNotes/justification (brief):\n- server_access_router is advertising the server subnet (10.200.0.0/24) into OSPF, enabling direct host->backend reachability and causing the segmentation/policy violation — mapped to an OSPF/area advertisement misconfiguration.\n- load_balancer shows application-layer latency (TTFB ~270 ms) and has an unusual secondary IP (20.200.0.1); the latency suggests potential load or application processing issues — mapped to load_balancer_overload (or processing delay) as a likely contributing root cause.\n\nIf you want, I can now:\n- produce the targeted configuration lines that advertise 10.200.0.0/24 in OSPF,\n- collect ACLs/firewall rules on server_access_router and load_balancer,\n- run traceroutes or further app-layer diagnostics to refine the load balancer/root cause diagnosis.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2889, "output_tokens": 233, "total_tokens": 3122, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2816}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
